Comment: 0,0:00:00.09,0:00:02.29,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}英文字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.09,0:00:02.29,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hi, it's me, Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.09,0:00:02.29,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}嗨 我是Tim Dodd 每日宇航员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.44,0:00:07.32,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as you probably know, NASA is working really hard on getting humans back to the surface of the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.44,0:00:07.32,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}你可能知道 NASA正努力让人类回到月球表面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.62,0:00:12.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And if all goes well, we could see this happen as early as 2024.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.62,0:00:12.18,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}如果一切顺利 最早可在2024年看到这一切发生
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:17.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And although I don't personally think that timeline is too likely to hold,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:17.18,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}虽然我个人认为这条时间表不太可能保持得住
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.49,0:00:21.02,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we haven't seen such an ambitious timeline for getting humans to the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.49,0:00:21.02,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}我们还没有看到过如此艰巨的载人登月时间表
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.10,0:00:23.71,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}since the Apollo program, back in the 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.10,0:00:23.71,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}自上世纪60年代的阿波罗计划以来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:26.03,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Not to mention the hardware exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:26.03,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}更不用说设备的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.31,0:00:30.57,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Checks have been written and the astronauts are training to spend time on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.31,0:00:30.57,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}支票已经开出 宇航员正在接受训练 以便在月球上度过一段时间
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.03,0:00:32.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's an exciting time to be alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.03,0:00:32.97,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}活在这个时代令人兴奋
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.97,0:00:34.49,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but unlike the Apollo program,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.97,0:00:34.49,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但与阿波罗计划不同的是
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.49,0:00:38.89,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which wound up putting 12 humans on the surface of the moon at an astronomical cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.49,0:00:38.89,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}（阿波罗计划最终以天文数字的费用将12名人类送上了月球表面）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:44.24,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Artemis promises to be a sustainable program with an eventual lunar outpost
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:44.24,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}阿尔忒弥斯有望成为一个可持续发展的计划 并最终建立一个月球基地
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.28,0:00:48.51,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and a permanent human presence at the Shackleton Crater on the South pole of the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.28,0:00:48.51,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}并在月球南极的沙克尔顿环形山 建立永久的人类存在
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.02,0:00:52.26,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yeah, that's right now we're talking. I mean, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.02,0:00:52.26,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}是啊 这才是有趣的地方 我是指 得了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:54.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is the 21st century.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:54.18,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}这是21世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:58.30,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You'd sure hope we can get back to the moon cheaper, using better technology
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:58.30,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}你肯定希望我们能用更好的技术 更便宜地回到月球
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:02.61,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and do it in a safer way than we did in the 1960s. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:02.61,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}同时还比60年代的方法更安全 对不对？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:06.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Right? So today we're going to answer the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:06.70,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}对不对？所以今天我们要回答这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.20,0:01:10.29,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Why does NASA think Artemis will be a sustainable program
