Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:20.46,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}可以做得特别精简 甚至连着陆腿都是那么的脆弱
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.89,0:05:23.31,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they wouldn't even hold the craft up on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.89,0:05:23.31,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}脆弱到在地球重力下连飞船自身都撑不起来
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:27.56,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because they're designed to only be used on the moon with its lower gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:27.56,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}因为在设计上 着陆腿只能在重力较低的月球上使用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.75,0:05:30.95,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The command module is where the astronauts hang out during the majority of the mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.75,0:05:30.95,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}指令舱是宇航员在大部分任务中的活动场所
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.07,0:05:34.34,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it's especially important during ascent and re-entry,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.07,0:05:34.34,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但在上升和再入时尤为重要
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:39.35,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4\pos(960,100)}because sitting on top of what's essentially a giant bomb with a nozzle is quite dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:39.35,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,980)}因为本质上宇航员是坐在是一个带有喷嘴的巨大炸弹的顶部 是相当危险的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.71,0:05:44.65,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}having a command module that can abort safely is generally considered a very good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.71,0:05:44.65,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}通常情况下指令舱最好可以安全地中止发射
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.69,0:05:48.99,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, of course, I've already done way too many videos on abort systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.69,0:05:48.99,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}那么 当然 我已经做了太多关于中止系统的视频
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.02,0:05:52.60,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including the one about the Gemini capsule's ejection seats,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.02,0:05:52.60,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}包括关于双子座指令舱的弹射座椅的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:57.60,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}another one about why SpaceX and Boeing are now using liquid fueled systems
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:57.60,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}另一个关于为什么SpaceX和波音(在逃逸系统上)使用液体燃料系统的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.97,0:06:03.27,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and even why Starship doesn't seem to have an abort system and whether or not it should.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.97,0:06:03.27,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}甚至是关于为什么Starship好像没有中止系统以及是否应该有中止系统的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.72,0:06:06.92,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So if you want to know anything about abort systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.72,0:06:06.92,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}所以如果你想了解任何关于中止系统的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:08.25,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I've definitely got you covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:08.25,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}我肯定已经提到了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.32,0:06:10.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And unlike the Lunar Lander,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.32,0:06:10.18,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}而且和登月舱不同的是
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:13.12,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the command module needs to handle atmospheric flight,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:13.12,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}指令舱需要应对大气层中的飞行
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:16.79,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}specifically the brutal reentry heat and landing portions of the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:16.79,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}特别是任务中残酷的再入热和着陆部分
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:21.90,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For these two programs, the command module's utilize an ablative heat shield,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:21.90,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}在这两个计划中 指令舱使用了一个烧蚀性隔热板
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.12,0:06:26.12,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which intentionally flakes off material taking heat away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.12,0:06:26.12,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}烧蚀性隔热板是指故意让材料剥落并带走热量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:29.28,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay, so let's pull up both systems that will be taking humans to the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:29.28,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}好了 那让我们把两个登月系统都拉出来溜溜
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.56,0:06:31.54,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}starting with the command modules.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.56,0:06:31.54,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}从指令舱开始
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:37.20,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Although they might look similar, the Apollo capsule and the Orion capsule are quite different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:37.20,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然它们看起来很相似 但阿波罗指令舱和猎户座指令舱有很大的不同
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.38,0:06:42.23,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Orion capsule is five meters wide versus the Apollo capsule's 3. 9 meters wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.38,0:06:42.23,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猎户座指令舱有5m宽 而阿波罗指令舱只有3.9m宽
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.71,0:06:49.41,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It sports an impressive nine cubic meters of habitable volume compared to 6. 2 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.71,0:06:49.41,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的可居住容积为9m³ 而阿波罗指令舱只有6.2m³
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.50,0:06:51.58,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it's around 50% more volume,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.50,0:06:51.58,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 它的体积大约多了50%
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.58,0:06:56.21,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it's quite a bit more roomy obviously and capable of up to 6 astronauts,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.58,0:06:56.21,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且它的空间明显大了不少 能够容纳6名宇航员
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:07:01.77,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}although it'll probably only fly four for the Artemis missions versus the Apollo's three,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:07:01.77,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然在阿尔忒弥斯任务中只会容纳4人 而阿波罗则为3人
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:07.25,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which the Apollo capsule could technically fit five astronauts for rescue missions,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:07.25,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其中阿波罗指令舱在技术上可以容纳5名宇航员进行救援任务
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:08.79,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but just barely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:08.79,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但只是勉强
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:12.31,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But what might be surprising is each vehicle's mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:12.31,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但可能让人惊讶的是每个航天器的质量
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:18.95,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Orion capsule and its service module are 26,520 kilograms fully fueled,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:18.95,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}猎户座指令舱和它的服务舱完全加满燃料的质量是26.52t
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.36,0:07:27.79,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is surprisingly lighter than the Apollo capsule and its service module, which are 28,800 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.36,0:07:27.79,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}竟然比阿波罗指令舱及其服务舱轻了2.28t
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.68,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But just looking at these two,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.68,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但只看这俩(外观)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:32.43,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you can tell they're basically backwards from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:32.43,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你会发现它俩基本上是相反的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.68,0:07:37.04,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Apollo command module was pretty small and had a large service module.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.68,0:07:37.04,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}阿波罗指令舱是相当小的 但服务舱较大
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:39.83,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And Orion is pretty much the opposite of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:39.83,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而猎户座差不多就是这种搭配的反面
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.13,0:07:44.14,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}a pretty large command module and a relatively small service module.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.13,0:07:44.14,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是一个相当大的指令舱和一个相对较小的服务舱
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:48.91,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This means the Orion capsule and its service module have much less Delta-v
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:48.91,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这意味着猎户座指令舱及其服务舱的速度增量(dv)值要少得多
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:53.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or the ability to change its velocity than the Apollo capsule and service module.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:53.70,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}或者说 比起阿波罗的指令舱和服务舱 其改变速度的能力差不少
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.13,0:07:56.67,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In fact, the Orion capsule and the service module
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.13,0:07:56.67,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上 猎户座的指令舱和服务舱
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:08:01.58,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}doesn't even have enough Delta-v to get into an out of low lunar orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:08:01.58,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至没有足够的dv(从地月转移轨道)往返月球低轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:05.20,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with only around 1,200 meters per second of Delta-v
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:05.20,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其dv只有1200m/s左右
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.39,0:08:07.27,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}versus the Apollo capsule and its service module,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.39,0:08:07.27,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对比阿波罗指令舱和服务舱
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:12.41,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which had over twice as much at around 2, 800 meters per second of Delta-v.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:12.41,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的dv有猎户座的两倍多 达到了2800m/s
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:17.37,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For those unfamiliar, Delta-v is how much a spacecraft can change its velocity in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:17.37,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}对于那些不熟悉的人来说 dv是指航天器在太空中的速度变化幅度
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.75,0:08:20.20,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a combination of the mass of the vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.75,0:08:20.20,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它考虑了航天器的质量
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.44,0:08:22.58,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the mass of the payload and the mass of the propellant,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.44,0:08:22.58,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}有效载荷的质量和推进剂的质量
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.90,0:08:27.49,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}mixed with the amount of fuel available to burn and the efficiency of the engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.90,0:08:27.49,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}再加上可供点火的燃料质量和发动机的效率
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:31.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So you can kind of think of it in the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:31.05,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}所以 你可以用以下方式近似地看待它
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.08,0:08:35.07,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as the range of a car which factors in the efficiency of the engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.08,0:08:35.07,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}如同汽车的续航里程会考虑发动机效率
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.21,0:08:39.15,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the size of the fuel tank and how much the car to push around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.21,0:08:39.15,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}油箱的大小和油门的大小
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.32,0:08:42.19,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, if you're a little bit confused on why we're talking about Delta-v
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.32,0:08:42.19,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}现在 如果你仍然搞不清楚我们为什么要讨论dv的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:44.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you still don't really get it, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:44.44,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}那么别担心
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.89,0:08:48.31,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It will get less confusing, cause we're going to show you why this matters,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.89,0:08:48.31,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}后面会讲到为什么这很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:52.14,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because this little fact right here makes a huge difference in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:52.14,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}因为dv这件事
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.14,0:08:54.17,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}how each system gets astronauts to the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.14,0:08:54.17,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}会很大地影响载人登月的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.41,0:08:58.14,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and why orbits of these two programs are extremely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.41,0:08:58.14,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}或者说很大地影响登月的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.41,0:09:00.39,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay. So speaking of extremely different,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.41,0:09:00.39,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}好吧 所以说到极度不同
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.78,0:09:03.12,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}let's look at the Lunar Landers next.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.78,0:09:03.12,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}接下来让我们看看登月舱
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:07.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this is going to be fun to talk about because we actually get to talk about four different Lunar Landers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:07.62,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}这将是一个有趣的话题 因为我们实际上要讨论四个不同的登月舱
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:12.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Since there's currently three Lunar Landers selected for development for the Artemis program.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:12.44,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}因为目前有三台登月舱被选为阿尔忒弥斯计划的开发对象
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.62,0:09:13.33,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For the Apollo program,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.62,0:09:13.33,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}对于阿波罗计划
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:19.52,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}of course we have that iconic Apollo lunar module sometimes called the LEM or lunar excursion module.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:19.52,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}当然 我们有那个标志性的阿波罗月球舱 有时也被称为LEM或月球游览舱
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:22.67,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This spidery looking vehicle produced by Grumman
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:22.67,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}这个由格鲁曼公司生产的看起来像蜘蛛一样的航天器
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.69,0:09:26.96,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}stood seven meters tall, 9.4 meters wide with its legs extended
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.69,0:09:26.96,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}展开着陆腿的情况下 高7m 宽9.4m
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.12,0:09:31.43,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and weighed up to 16,400 kilograms, fully fueled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.12,0:09:31.43,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}加满燃料后重达16.4t
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:36.51,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It could carry two astronauts to the surface of the moon for up to 75 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:36.51,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它可以载着两名宇航员在月球表面停留75小时
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.58,0:09:38.79,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For the Artemis program, we have the human landing system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.58,0:09:38.79,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}对于阿尔忒弥斯计划 我们有载人登月系统
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:40.94,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is a set of commercial contracts,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:40.94,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}这是一套商业合同
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.19,0:09:44.54,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}more akin to the Commercial Crew Program than it is SLS and Orion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.19,0:09:44.54,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}比起SLS和猎户座 它更类似于商业载人计划
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:48.10,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So basically NASA left out any strict guidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:48.10,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}所以 NASA基本上没有设置任何严格的准则
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.13,0:09:53.74,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and accepted bids that thought they could get a system to the moon within that ambitious 2024 timeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.13,0:09:53.74,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}接受符合要求的投标 也就是他们认为 可在2024年这个艰巨的时间表内登月的那种
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.91,0:09:57.19,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At the moment, we don't have a ton of details on all these systems yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.91,0:09:57.19,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}目前 我们还没有这些系统的大量细节
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:09:57.91,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:09:57.91,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 就目前而言
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:02.28,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we're just going to put up a rough size estimation of all these systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:02.28,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们只要把这些系统的粗略估计的尺寸放在这
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.46,0:10:06.62,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're intended to have up to four astronauts for up to two weeks per mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.46,0:10:06.62,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们的目的是让四名宇航员 在每次任务中最多停留两周
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:09.82,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Currently there's three incredibly different vehicles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:09.82,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}目前有三种非常不同的航天器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.82,0:10:13.56,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Although NASA might down-select to two in 2021,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.82,0:10:13.56,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管NASA可能会在2021年减少到两艘飞船
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.95,0:10:17.00,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the three currently chosen and into the next phase of development
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.95,0:10:17.00,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但目前还是选定了三个项目 且能进入下一阶段的发展的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.34,0:10:23.30,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}are the Blue Origin led National Team, Dynetics and SpaceX with a lunar version of their Starship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.34,0:10:23.30,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}也就是蓝色起源领导的国家队 Dynetics和SpaceX的月球版Starship
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.32,0:10:27.07,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The National Team Lander features a Blue Origin Lander stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.32,0:10:27.07,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}在国家队登月器中 蓝色起源负责开发下降级(着陆级)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:31.80,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}a Lockheed Martin ascent stage, a Northrop Grumman transfer element vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:31.80,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}洛克希德马丁负责上升级 诺斯罗普格鲁曼负责转移级
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.80,0:10:35.50,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and Draper developing the descent guidance and flight avionics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.80,0:10:35.50,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}以及德雷珀负责的下降制导和飞控设备
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:40.45,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The system is about two thirds reusable with only the lunar lander portion being used once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:40.45,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}该系统大约有三分之二可以重复使用 只有下降级部分是一次性的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.72,0:10:45.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At first, although I speculate it could eventually be refueled on the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.72,0:10:45.70,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}当然 一开始时下降级是一次性的 尽管我推测它最终可以在月球表面重新加注燃料
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:50.10,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and if there's enough Delta-v they could maybe reuse the Lander as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:50.10,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}如果有足够的dv 他们可能会重复使用着陆器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.88,0:10:51.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.88,0:10:51.62,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}我也不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:56.16,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The National Team Lander will likely fly on a few of Blue Origin's New Glenn rockets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:56.16,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}国家队着陆器很可能会用几枚蓝色起源的新格伦火箭进行发射
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.20,0:10:59.07,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it might fly on some other rockets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.20,0:10:59.07,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但也可能用别的火箭发射
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:05.50,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including segments being flown as co-manifest payloads on an upgraded SLS Block 1-B
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:05.50,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}比如将国家队着陆器部件中的几个 作为SLS的升级版Block 1-B的共同载荷进行发射
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.99,0:11:08.52,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}We don't really have those details yet though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.99,0:11:08.52,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}不过我们还没有真正掌握这些细节
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.52,0:11:13.49,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Dynetics Lander is a low slung, perhaps wiener-dog-esque lunar lander.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.52,0:11:13.49,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}Dynetics登陆器是一个低矮的 腊肠狗式的登月舱
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:18.39,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And it's a very unique looking thing here with over 20 subcontractors
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:18.39,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它的外观非常独特 有20多个分包商参与其中
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:23.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the most notable being Draper, Sierra Nevada, United launch Alliance, And Thales Alenia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:23.44,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}最著名的有德雷珀 内华达山脉 联合发射联盟(ULA)和泰雷兹阿莱尼亚公司
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:27.29,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It features eight landing engines that are fully reusable for multiple missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:27.29,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它带有8个可重复使用的着陆发动机 可以执行多次任务
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:32.69,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}With the only thing thrown away with each landing is a simple pair of fuel tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:32.69,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}每次着陆时唯一被扔掉的就是一对简单的燃料箱
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.78,0:11:36.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Lander can fit on a single SLS 1B cargo version,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.78,0:11:36.70,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}着陆器可以装在一个SLS 1B货运版上
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:41.74,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or they also mentioned it could be flown in segments on ULA's upcoming Vulcan rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:41.74,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}或者他们也提到还可以在ULA未来的火神火箭上分段发射
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.19,0:11:44.45,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I am not really sure how many launches did take,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.19,0:11:44.45,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}我不太清楚这到底要分几次发射
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.50,0:11:50.65,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but I'm guessing it have to be like at least two Vulcans to get a Lander of that size to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.50,0:11:50.65,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但我觉得至少要两枚火神火箭 才能把这么大的着陆器运到月球上
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:53.44,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Lastly, to the shock of pretty much everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:53.44,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}最后 令所有人震惊的是
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.80,0:11:57.42,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA chose SpaceX's Starship as an option too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.80,0:11:57.42,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}NASA也选择了SpaceX的Starship
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:12:00.04,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this version is a Lunar Lander only,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:12:00.04,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}现在这个版本专用于登月
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:03.68,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it's missing the aerodynamic features and additional heat shielding,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:03.68,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}也就缺少了空气动力学特性和额外的隔热板
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:07.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but also includes bonus landing engines near the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:07.05,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但也增加了靠近顶部的着陆发动机
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.38,0:12:10.14,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now Starship's reuse confuses me quite a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.38,0:12:10.14,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}那么Starship的重复使用让我颇为不解
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:12.98,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because I mean, for sure it'd be an awesome just outpost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:12.98,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}因为我是指 它肯定很棒 哪怕只是作为基地使用
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:14.04,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Just keep that thing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:14.04,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}只要把那玩意儿放在那儿
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.07,0:12:17.46,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You have like a thousand cubic meters of habitable volume. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.07,0:12:17.46,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}你就有一个上千立方米的可居住空间了 没错
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.47,0:12:19.38,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Just land it once and never touch it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.47,0:12:19.38,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}只要降落一次 然后再别动它
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:22.28,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If you are to refly it and reuse it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:22.28,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}如果你要重新发射并重复使用它
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.62,0:12:27.37,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it actually has to go all the way back to probably low Earth orbit or at least Earth's orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.62,0:12:27.37,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它实际上得要返回低地球轨道 或者地球轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.71,0:12:34.53,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and be refueled through multiple refueling flights of a Starship tanker, which is no small feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.71,0:12:34.53,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}并通过燃料版Starship的多次发射进行燃料补加 这可不是什么小事
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:39.85,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this does mean in order to pull off each and every mission, including the very first one,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:39.85,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}所以 这确实意味着为了完成每一次任务 包括第一次任务
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:45.82,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's going to have to be many full stack, Super Heavy Starship launches back to back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:45.82,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它将不得不使用很多全功能的 包含超重助推器的Starship并连续进行发射
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.14,0:12:48.25,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now we'll get more into this in a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.14,0:12:48.25,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}那么 不久后会细讲这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:51.83,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And in an upcoming video, we'll also talk about this a ton,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:51.83,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}在那个视频中 真的会讲很多关于Starship月球版的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.83,0:12:54.76,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because we're going to be going over all the different payload options
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.83,0:12:54.76,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}因为我们要讨论所有不同的有效载荷选项
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.13,0:12:56.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}for getting Starship stuff to the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.13,0:12:56.97,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}也就是Starship到月球的运载能力
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.97,0:13:01.34,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including refueling Starship versus kick stages, we're going to dive in really, really deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.97,0:13:01.34,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}包括Starship的燃料补加对比上面级的使用 我们会深入研究 非常非常深入
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:02.11,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:02.11,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}我保证
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:07.27,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}After the next phase of selection and more detailed proposals scheduled for February, 2021,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:07.27,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}在2021年2月进行下一阶段的选择和更详细的提案的程序之后
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.63,0:13:12.05,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we can do an update truly comparing the three Landers in this human landing system.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.63,0:13:12.05,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}可以做一个更新的视频 真正比较一下这个载人登月系统中的三个登月舱
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:14.74,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So just keep in mind that for the Artemis program,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:14.74,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}那么(对于以上这么多信息) 只要记住 对于阿尔忒弥斯计划
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.05,0:13:18.64,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}each of these Lunar Landers requires its own ride to the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.05,0:13:18.64,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}每个登月舱都需要独立发射
