Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.78,0:13:23.70,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}换句话说就是不能和宇航员搭乘的火箭一起发射
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.70,0:13:26.58,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}like the Apollo program did with the Saturn V.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.70,0:13:26.58,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}也就与阿波罗计划中的土星五号不同
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.58,0:13:27.88,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Lastly, the rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.58,0:13:27.88,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}最后 火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:30.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}As you know, from my last video,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:30.18,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}如你所知 在我上一个视频中
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.18,0:13:34.74,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the Artemis program will be utilizing the space launch system or the SLS rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.18,0:13:34.74,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}阿尔忒弥斯计划将使用太空发射系统 简称SLS火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:38.18,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to carry the Orion capsule and its service module to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:38.18,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}将猎户座指令舱及其服务舱送上月球
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.37,0:13:41.79,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Apollo program utilized the mighty Saturn V,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.37,0:13:41.79,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}阿波罗计划使用了强大的土星五号
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:47.13,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which could carry the Apollo command module and service module and the lunar module.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:47.13,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它可以携带阿波罗指令舱和服务舱 以及月球舱
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:50.21,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now as a refresher, here's the specs of these main rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:50.21,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在 也可以复习下 这里是这些主要火箭的规格
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:56.70,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For the SLS, we're going to show you both the Block 1 and the Block 1B upgrade that may fly on later missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:56.70,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}对于SLS 我们将向你展示Block 1 以及可能在以后的任务中发射的升级版Block 1B
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:14:01.97,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Regardless, their lift off thrust is the same at 39.1 Mega Newtons,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:14:01.97,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这两种SLS的起飞推力都是一样的 为39.1MN(兆牛)(约3989.8t推力)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:06.51,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is above the Saturn V's 35.1 Mega Newtons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:06.51,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这高于土星五号的35.1MN(约3581.6t推力)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:13.69,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The LEO capacity for SLS is 95 tons or slightly more at 97 tons for the Block 1B
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:13.69,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS的近地轨道(LEO)运载能力为95t 而Block 1B的LEO运载能力略高 为97t
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.75,0:14:17.58,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the Saturn V could put 140 tons into LEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.75,0:14:17.58,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而土星五号的LEO运载能力(*)为140t
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.85,0:14:21.14,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The upgrade to the SLS 1B doesn't change the LEO capacity much
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.85,0:14:21.14,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}升级到SLS 1B后 LEO运载能力不会有太大变化
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.18,0:14:24.79,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because core stage pretty much puts the upper stage into LEO
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.18,0:14:24.79,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}因为芯一级几乎是把上面级放到了LEO上
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.95,0:14:26.84,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as we'll talk about more here in a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.95,0:14:26.84,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}过一会我们会更进一步讨论
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:29.93,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but by having a more capable stage in low Earth orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:29.93,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但是芯级的LEO运载能力更强
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.96,0:14:33.75,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it means the trans lunar injection capacity can increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.96,0:14:33.75,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}也就意味着月球轨道进入能力可以增加(在上面级不拉垮的情况下)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:36.64,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And we call this the TLI capacity,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:36.64,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}简称TLI能力
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.90,0:14:41.68,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it's just a measure of how much mass can the rocket send on a trajectory to the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.90,0:14:41.68,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}TLI是指火箭能把多少质量的载荷送到地月转移轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.06,0:14:45.62,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but not necessarily put in lunar orbit or land on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.06,0:14:45.62,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}但不是送入绕月轨道 或者在月球着陆
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:48.93,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's just what it can shoot out towards the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:48.93,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}只是飞掠月球的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:55.32,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And notice the Block 1B four RL-10's on its much bigger Exploration Upper Stage
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:55.32,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}注意 Block 1B的上面级 探索上面级更大 有着4个RL-10
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:14:57.97,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}compared to the Block 1 of SLS,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:14:57.97,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}而SLS Block 1的上面级就小一些
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:02.60,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which only has a single RL-10 on the smaller Interim Cryogenic Propulsion Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:02.60,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}它的过渡型低温上面级上 只有一个RL-10
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:10.11,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So that's why we see the difference here with the TLI performance of SLS at 27 tons or 43 tons with the Block 1B
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:10.11,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 这就是为什么这里会标注两种TLI性能 Block 1的是27t Block 1B的是43t
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.40,0:15:13.46,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the Saturn V was 48.6 tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.40,0:15:13.46,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而土星五号的TLI(*)是48.6t
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.75,0:15:20.89,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yes, it's really confusing that the less powerful Saturn V actually has more capability than SLS,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.75,0:15:20.89,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是的 性能较差的土星五号居然比SLS的能力更强 这真的很让人困惑
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.26,0:15:23.50,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but having a three-stage rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.26,0:15:23.50,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但火箭是三级的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:29.67,1080P-shsb-58,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with two of those stages being huge high energy hydrogen stages definitely paid off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:29.67,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其中两级还是能量(比冲)较高的氢氧火箭 指定有好果汁吃噢
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.87,0:15:31.28,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And then of course in the Artemis program,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.87,0:15:31.28,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}当然 在阿尔忒弥斯计划中
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:35.40,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we'll see an array of other launch vehicles from Starship to Vulcan to New Glenn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:35.40,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}我们会看到一系列其他的运载火箭 从Starship到火神再到新格伦
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:41.54,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And who knows, maybe even some new rockets or smaller rockets might end up playing a part in the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:41.54,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}谁知道呢 甚至一些新火箭或者更小的火箭最终也会在这个计划中发挥作用
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:45.83,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So these two programs have extremely different hardware choices and capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:45.83,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}所以这两个计划的设备选择和运载能力都极为不同
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.34,0:15:49.78,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So you'd probably think these hardware choices affect the missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.34,0:15:49.78,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}那么你可能会认为这些设备选择会影响到任务
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:53.02,1080P-shsb-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They sure do and boy are they different!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:53.02,1080P-shsm-75,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\pos(960,1020)}没错 是会影响到任务 但是老兄 它们不一样
